    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don’t like raw garlic? Use half!), <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span>[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>yoghurt</strong> <strong>Caesar dressing</strong></p><p>Remove the base of your <strong>lettuce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
